The paper deals with network coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It specifically focuses on linear network coding, which is a subfield of network coding that involves linear combinations of packets. The paper also discusses the construction of networks and the use of linear rank inequalities, which are topics in network information theory (cs.NI) and network science (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the use of finite fields, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses upper-bounds on the linear coding capacity of networks, which is a topic in complexity theory (cs.CC).
